{
  "documentMetadata": {
    "title": "Human Bite Wound",
    "sourceFile": "Bite_ Human.pdf",
    "lastUpdated": "2025-01-06"
  },
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Clinical Setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Cleaning, irrigation and debridement are most important.",
        "For clenched fist or hand injuries, x-rays should be obtained.",
        "For bites inflicted by hospitalized patients, consider aerobic Gram-negative bacilli.",
        "X-ray to evaluate for fracture or foreign body.",
        "Potential risk of transmitting blood-borne pathogens if injury contaminated with another's blood.",
        "Review tetanus status."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Etiologies"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Streptococci",
        "Staphylococcus aureus",
        "Eikenella corrodens",
        "Fusobacterium sp.",
        "Peptostreptococcus sp. (Peptoniphilus sp.)",
        "Prevotella sp.",
        "Porphyromonas sp."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Primary Regimens"
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Early (wound not yet infected):"
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Amoxicillin-clavulanate",
                "dose": "875/125 mg",
                "route": "po",
                "frequency": "bid"
              }
            ],
            "durationDetail": {
              "fixedDuration": "5 days"
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Later (signs of infection, usually 3-24 hours):"
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Ampicillin-sulbactam",
                "dose": "3 gm",
                "route": "IV",
                "frequency": "q6h"
              },
              {
                "connector": "or",
                "drug": "Cefoxitin",
                "dose": "2 gm",
                "route": "IV",
                "frequency": "q8h"
              },
              {
                "connector": "OR",
                "drug": "Piperacillin-tazobactam",
                "dose": "4.5 gm",
                "route": "IV",
                "frequency": "q8h",
                "notes": "over 4 hr"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "condition": "For serious infections, until MRSA is excluded",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Vancomycin",
                "dose": "1 gm",
                "route": "IV",
                "frequency": "q12h",
                "notes": "or 1.5 gm q12h if wt >100 kg"
              },
              {
                "connector": "or",
                "drug": "Daptomycin",
                "dose": "6 mg/kg",
                "route": "IV",
                "frequency": "q24h"
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Alternative Regimens"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "A carbapenem can be used in place of Ampicillin-sulbactam, Cefoxitin, or Piperacillin-tazobactam if parenteral therapy is required"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "drugRegimen",
      "regimenData": {
        "condition": "If patient is Penicillin allergic",
        "components": [
          {
            "drug": "Clindamycin"
          },
          {
            "connector": "+",
            "drug": "(Ciprofloxacin or Levofloxacin or Moxifloxacin)"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "drugRegimen",
      "regimenData": {
        "notes": "non-US",
        "components": [
          {
            "drug": "Amoxicillin-clavulanate",
            "dose": "1000 mg-200 mg",
            "route": "IV",
            "frequency": "q8h"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Comments"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "For a review of bacteriology of human bite wounds, see Clin Infect Dis 37:1481, 2003; treatment see https://www.idsociety.org/practice-guideline/skin-and-soft-tissue-infections/.",
        "Eikenella spp.\nSusceptible to: Fluoroquinolones and Beta-Lactam / Beta-lactamase inhibitor combinations: e.g., Ampicillin-sulbactam.\nResistant to: Clindamycin, Nafcillin/Oxacillin, Metronidazole, Cephalexin/Cefazolin, TMP/SMX, Aminoglycosides and Erythromycin.",
        "Recommend treatment with Amoxicillin-clavulanate, Ampicillin-sulbactam, or Ertapenem; if allergic/intolerant to B-lactam, treat with Fluoroquinolone monotherapy",
        "Clenched fist (and other hand) bite wounds pose risk for deep infections (e.g., bone, joint, tendon sheath) and require careful evaluation."
      ]
    }
  ]
}